The paper deals with formal verification using model checking, which is a topic in computer science. The focus is on infinite transition systems and their synchronization constraints, which suggests categories such as cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.LT (Automata and Formal Languages). The paper also discusses the expressive power of first-order logic and its extensions, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper introduces finitely synchronized transition systems, which could relate to categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
